---
title: Sarh — Digital ID card issuance sequence
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Officer as ID Issuer<br/>Officer
    actor Citizen as Citizen
    participant Web as ID-Issuer Station<br/>(Angular)
    participant API as .NET 8 API
    participant DB as SQL Server
    participant NFC as NTAG 424 DNA<br/>Reader
    participant SSI as ACA-Py<br/>(SSI agent)
    participant Print as Card Printer

    Officer->>Web: opens Issue station
    Citizen->>Officer: presents legacy paper ID
    Officer->>Web: Step 1 — enters identity
    Officer->>Web: Step 2 — captures photo
    Officer->>Web: Step 3 — captures signature
    Officer->>Web: Step 4 — fingerprint (optional)
    Officer->>Web: Step 5 — review
    Web->>API: POST /api/v1/citizens<br/>{name, dob, region, photo}
    API->>DB: INSERT citizen, audit_log
    DB-->>API: { citizen_id, digital_id_number }
    API-->>Web: 201 Created

    Web->>Web: navigate /finalize
    Officer->>Web: clicks "Issue & Encode"
    Web->>API: POST /api/v1/digital-id-cards
    API->>DB: INSERT digital_id_cards
    API->>DB: INSERT nfc_card_secrets<br/>(AES-GCM wrapped keys)
    API->>SSI: create_did + issue VC<br/>type=CitizenIdentity
    SSI-->>API: { did, credential_id }
    API->>DB: UPDATE card SET did, vc_id
    API-->>Web: 200 { card, nfc_keys, sun_url_template }

    Web->>NFC: encode_card(uid, keys, SUN URL)
    NFC-->>Web: write_ok=true
    Web->>API: POST /api/v1/digital-id-cards/{id}/confirm-encoded
    API->>DB: INSERT id_issuance_history (action=issue)
    API->>DB: INSERT audit_log

    Web->>Print: render PDF + send to printer
    Print-->>Officer: physical card
    Officer->>Citizen: hands card

    Note over Citizen,API: Public verify: tap card →<br/>verify.sarh.ly/{sun} resolves SDM<br/>+ checks rolling counter
